image.altText: Sam Kerr claps

items.synopsis: The Matildas and France can't be separated after 90 minutes of action in a tense FIFA Women's World Cup quarterfinal in Brisbane, with extra time required to split the sides. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: France has goal ruled out in extra time during tense Women's World Cup quarterfinal in Brisbane

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Vicki Becho and Dali Kenza combined well to end the first half of extra time, but Mackenzie Arnold came to Australia's rescue. Just. It does feel like the Matildas are holding on. Even the chances they've created have been pretty haphazard rather than some masterful plan. But it's still 0-0. They're still creating those chances. Penalties?
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: One period of extra time down. It's still 0-0!

children.content: Vicki Becho and Dali Kenza combined well to end the first half of extra time, but Mackenzie Arnold came to Australia's rescue. Just.
It does feel like the Matildas are holding on. Even the chances they've created have been pretty haphazard rather than some masterful plan.
But it's still 0-0. They're still creating those chances.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Alanna Kennedy has scored a shocking own goal off a corner that clearly should have been a goal kick. She just headed straight past Mackenzie Arnold has she tried to clear. But French captain Wendie Renard is called for dragging down Caitlin Foord in the box. A HUGE let-off for Australia. And the right call in the end.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 100' Australia scores an own goal, but the ref saves them!

children.content: Alanna Kennedy has scored a shocking own goal off a corner that clearly should have been a goal kick. She just headed straight past Mackenzie Arnold has she tried to clear.
But French captain Wendie Renard is called for dragging down Caitlin Foord in the box.
A HUGE let-off for Australia. And the right call in the end.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: What a game this has been. Proper ebbing, flowing, surging contest with neither team on top for long. France definitely finished the game stronger, so it will be interesting to see how Tony Gustavsson uses his bench. Steph Catley and Alanna Kennedy were immense in that second half to deny the French raids, and Sam Kerr really has injected an extra element to the Matildas since coming on.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: WE'RE HEADING TO EXTRA TIME!
